@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

Shortly I wanted to have a program that displays a Button menu but is not too
big and still quite flexible. I found some programs on Aminet and on the Fred
Fish CDs but either they did not look as I wanted too or the GUI was quite bad
or they lacked features which I wanted to have.

At that time I already was familar with the @{"BGUI" link "BGUI" 0} GUI creation library
and decided to use it because I knew how simply it is to create GUIs with it.
With that I only needed a few days to create the program and I'm quite satis-
fied with the result. I used a program called @{"JMenu" link "JMenu" 0} which was written under
OS1.3 and had some Mungwall hits but most of the features which I wished to
compare it as a base. The @{"menu" link "menuprefs" 0} definition file has a nearly backward
compatible format as @{"JMenu" link "JMenu" 0}'s menu definition file has.

The program was developed with SAS/C 6.55 on an A4000/040 so it should be and
because it ran stable I decided to release it. I have Kichstart 40.68 and run
Workbench 40.35, but I have used no special OS3.1 features, so it should run
on OS2.x platforms, too. If not, please tell me about it.

@endnode

